'As for you Mampintsha, your career is over. You think we're scared of you? Leave Babes alone, she's a child. You shouldn't even be dating her.' These are the words of kwaito musician Mshoza, who has reacted to the video that shows a man believed to be Mampintsha, physically abusing a woman believed to be Babes Wodumo. The video has been making rounds on social media was posted by Babes on her Instagram page, in the early hours of Monday morning. In a minute long video, Mshoza says Babes has not been taking her calls and urges her to "get out before it's too late." "Get out my love, while you're still beautiful, while you still have your esteem and while you're still confident. Don't wait until you're washed out before you can leave." Watch the video below: